## 🖼️ SLIDE 2 — Problem Statement

**Title:** The Problem

### Key Points:
- 🌍 Over 50% of farmers globally lack access to scientific crop planning tools
- ❌ Wrong crop selection leads to poor yields and economic loss
- 🌦️ Climate variability makes traditional knowledge unreliable
- 🧪 Soil nutrient data is rarely translated into actionable decisions

> **"Farmers need a smart, accessible system that turns soil and weather data into real crop recommendations."**

---

## 🖼️ SLIDE 3 — Objectives

**Title:** Project Objectives

| # | Objective |
|---|-----------|
| 1 | Predict the best crop using ML based on soil nutrients & climate |
| 2 | Integrate real-time weather data (OpenWeatherMap API) |
| 3 | Provide top-5 crop suggestions with confidence scores |
| 4 | Offer farming advisories based on conditions |
| 5 | Store history of recommendations for future reference |
| 6 | Deliver a clean, responsive web interface |

