## 🖼️ SLIDE 5 — Dataset & Machine Learning Model

**Title:** Data & ML Model

### Dataset ([crop_data.csv](file:///d:/crop%20project/backend/data/crop_data.csv))
- **Records:** 2,200 samples (100 per crop)
- **Classes:** 22 crops (Rice, Maize, Cotton, Coffee, Mango, etc.)
- **Features:** N, P, K (soil nutrients), Temperature, Humidity, pH, Rainfall

### Model: Random Forest Classifier
| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Algorithm | Random Forest |
| Trees (n_estimators) | 200 |
| Train/Test Split | 80% / 20% |
| Random State | 42 |
| Parallel Jobs | -1 (all CPU cores) |

### Performance
- ✅ Model Accuracy: **~99%** on test set
- Outputs: **Top-5 crop predictions with probability confidence scores**

---

## 🖼️ SLIDE 6 — MODULE 1: Input Module

**Title:** Module 1 — Input Collection

### What it does:
Gathers all agronomic and contextual data from the farmer.

### Input Fields:
| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| Nitrogen (N) | Number | Soil nitrogen content (mg/kg) |
| Phosphorus (P) | Number | Soil phosphorus content |
| Potassium (K) | Number | Soil potassium content |
| Temperature | Number | In °C |
| Humidity | Number | In % |
| pH Level | Number | Soil acidity (0–14) |
| Rainfall | Number | Annual rainfall (mm) |
| Location | Text | City/village for weather fetch |
| Soil Type | Dropdown | Alluvial, Black, Red, Sandy, Loamy… |
| Irrigation Type | Dropdown | Drip, Flood, Sprinkler, Rainfed |
| Land Size | Number | In acres |

### Frontend File: [frontend/index.html](file:///d:/crop%20project/frontend/index.html)
- Responsive form with grouped field sections
- Auto-fetches weather when user enters location (debounced)

---

## 🖼️ SLIDE 7 — MODULE 2: Processing Module (ML Engine)

**Title:** Module 2 — AI Processing Engine

### Flow:
```
Input Data (7 core features)
        │
        ▼
  Feature Vector: [N, P, K, Temp, Humidity, pH, Rainfall]
        │
        ▼
  Random Forest Model (200 Decision Trees)
        │
        ▼
  predict_proba() → Probabilities for all 22 crop classes
        │
        ▼
  Top-5 Crops sorted by confidence score
```

### Key Backend Logic ([backend/app.py](file:///d:/crop%20project/backend/app.py) → `/recommend` endpoint):
- Validates & converts all input to `float`
- Runs `rf_model.predict_proba(features)`
- Ranks crops using `np.argsort(proba)[::-1][:5]`
- Enriches result with emoji, description & fertilizer recommendation
- Calls [get_advisory()](file:///d:/crop%20project/backend/app.py#144-165) for weather-based tips
- Calls [get_soil_advisory()](file:///d:/crop%20project/backend/app.py#167-179) for soil-specific tips
- Saves result to SQLite via `save_recommendation()`

### Also handles optional context:
- Soil type → soil advisory
- Irrigation type → stored in DB
- Land size → stored in DB

---

## 🖼️ SLIDE 8 — MODULE 3: Output / Recommendation Module

**Title:** Module 3 — Recommendation Output

### What the system returns:

#### Top Recommendation Card:
| Field | Example |
|-------|---------|
| Crop Name | Rice 🌾 |
| Confidence | 89.5% |
| Description | Paddy crop, needs high water |
| Fertilizer | Urea + DAP |

#### All Recommendations (Top 5):
- Ranked list with confidence bars
- Each card shows: crop emoji, name, confidence %, description, fertilizer

#### Advisory Tips:
- **Weather advisories** based on Temp, Humidity & Rainfall:
  - > 35°C → irrigation warning
  - > 85% humidity → fungal disease warning
  - < 50mm rainfall → irrigation recommended
- **Soil advisories** based on soil type:
  - Laterite → lime pH fix
  - Sandy soil → frequent irrigation
  - Black soil → ideal for cotton

---

## 🖼️ SLIDE 9 — MODULE 4: Weather Module

**Title:** Module 4 — Real-Time Weather Integration

### Endpoints:
| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/weather?city=Mumbai` | GET | Current weather data |
| `/forecast?city=Mumbai` | GET | 4-day weather forecast |

### Current Weather Response:
- Temperature, Humidity, Rainfall, Wind Speed, Pressure
- Weather description & icon (☀️ ⛅ 🌧️)
- Auto-generated farming advisory

### 4-Day Forecast:
- Groups OWM 3-hour slots by day
- Per day: min/max temp, avg humidity, total rainfall, description

### Fallback:
- If no API key → returns **mock/demo data** so app still works for testing

### Used for:
- Auto-filling temperature, humidity, rainfall in the input form
- Weather Advisory section on the UI

---

## 🖼️ SLIDE 10 — MODULE 5: History Module

**Title:** Module 5 — Recommendation History

### Database: [recommendations.db](file:///d:/crop%20project/backend/recommendations.db) (SQLite)
### Schema stored by [backend/database.py](file:///d:/crop%20project/backend/database.py):

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | INTEGER | Auto-increment primary key |
| timestamp | TEXT | ISO datetime of recommendation |
| location | TEXT | City name |
| soil_type | TEXT | Soil category |
| irrigation | TEXT | Irrigation method |
| land_size | REAL | Acres |
| N, P, K | REAL | Nutrient values |
| temperature | REAL | °C |
| humidity | REAL | % |
| ph | REAL | pH value |
| rainfall | REAL | mm |
| top_crop | TEXT | Best recommended crop |
| confidence | REAL | Confidence % |
| all_results | TEXT | JSON of top-5 results |

### Endpoint: `GET /history`
- Returns last 20 recommendations
- Frontend renders them as full recommendation cards

---

## 🖼️ SLIDE 11 — API Endpoints Summary

**Title:** Backend API Reference

| Endpoint | Method | Input | Output |
|----------|--------|-------|--------|
| `/recommend` | POST | JSON: N,P,K, Temp, Humidity, pH, Rainfall, Location, Soil, Irrigation, Land size | Top crop + Top-5 list + Advisory |
| `/weather` | GET | `?city=CityName` | Temp, Humidity, Rainfall, Wind, Pressure, Icon, Advisory |
| `/forecast` | GET | `?city=CityName` | 4-day array: day, icon, min/max temp, humidity, rainfall |
| `/history` | GET | — | Last 20 saved recommendations |
| `/feature-importance` | GET | — | Feature importance scores from RF model |
| `/health` | GET | — | API status + crop count |

### Tech: Python · Flask · Flask-CORS · joblib · scikit-learn · NumPy

